The paper discusses the use of deep learning architectures for colorization and proposes a novel architecture for general colorization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of colorization for generating makeup suggestions, which involves image processing and artificial intelligence techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), graphics (cs.GR), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
